$ Excel: Worksheet functions that can be given a criteria

→ Microsoft/Office/Excel/functions[Worksheet functions] that can be given a criteria include
  • `averageIf()`, `averageIfs()`
  • `countIf()`, `countIfs()`
  • `dGet()`
  • `dProduct()`
  • `filter()`
  • `maxIfs()`, `mminfs()` (Is there no `maxIf()` or `minIf()`) ?
  • `sumIf()`, → Microsoft/Office/Excel/functions/sumifs[`sumIfs()`]


sa:
  The → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/AutoFilter[`autoFilter`] object.
